\n\nA lot of people have old shoes lying around. They are a bit boring and old fashioned and are rarely used. We are reluctant to throw them to avoid being wasteful, but in the end they are just old shoes piling up in our house.\n\n \n\nDo you have a pair of old shoes?\n\nDo you want to glam up your shoes?\n\nDo you want to give them a new birth?\n\n \n\nIf you just said \'yes\', then here we go-\n\nWith the following tips and tricks you can convert your old, granny shoes into glam shoes instantly. Or you can make previously unsuitable shoes match your new outfit. Or you can make one pair of shoes seem like several. From beautiful to fashionable, elaborating your shoes can be easy with the following simple ways.\n\nThe first step of your artsy mission is to acquire the ingredients. You just need some clip findings, ribbons, beads, lace, faux pearls, silk or paper flowers, clip on shoe accessories, rhinestones, cabochons and other tiny trinkets and don\'t forget contact cement and bobby pins to secure these things on your shoes.\n\nAfter you gather all bits and bytes you can, make your designs. Keep your designs simple. Just don\'t paste all stuff on one pair of shoes. Try to make different design with different color combinations for different pairs. However, you can have the same design for both the shoes of the same pair.\n\nThere are many ways to design simple tidbits. You can make a tailored bow (actually a pair would be better) from ribbons or you can give a romantic touch by affixing lace, a strand of faux pearls or delicate beaded trim around the opening of sandals. You can use studded rhinestones to attach the lace to add glitzy touch. You can also give a spring look to your sandals by affixing silk or paper flowers or butterflies and sea shells and more.\n\nEvery design doesnt have to be elegant. You can decorate as casually as you want. You can also use fabric paint designs on your shoes. Design making needs a lot of practice and once you are on you\'ll become better and better with time. Once you\'ve had a little practice you\'ll have the most extensive shoe wardrobe of anyone you know.\n\nWith this level of creativity your shoes can transform into customized, engaging compliments to your personality. You can also turn a pair of cheap pumps or flats into refined accessories for you ensembles, so you should learn to decorate your plain shoes to get the great look you desire. The next time you\'re considering a new pair of shoes thinks instead of redecorating a pair you already own and impress your friends with your creativity.","Getting creative with your old shoes","","inherit","open","open","","103-revision-6","","","2011-02-20 06:07:03","2011-02-20 06:07:03","","103","http://www.nethaat.com/blog/?p=127","0","revision","","0");
