\n\nDrawing is the creative translation of everything we observe sense or imagine. It represents the amazing ability of human beings to express them. With a pencil and piece of paper, one can craft out incredible masterpieces. Some people are naturally gifted; they are born to draw, while others struggle with simple line drawings. Most of them give up drawing in childhood and move on to pursue a career where ability to draw is seldom required. If you are one among those who throw the pencil down, then here are few tried, tested and proven ways to improve fix drawing skills.\n\nArt is not something that you learn sitting in front of your computer. Art, any form of it, takes patience, practice and perseverance. Drawing is no exception. If you want to draw better then you should draw everyday. Mastering any art takes sweat, so practice. Procrastination is your biggest enemy at this stage and it will try to hold you as prisoner. But if you want to get something out of your life, if you want to become an artist and if you want to get appreciated then you can take the pain. Practice whenever you get the chance. Draw when you are sitting idle. Draw instead of watching television, its more productive.\n\nAs soon as you train yourself to draw anytime- anywhere, move on to next step- draw from life. Draw the things you see instead of drawing from their photographs. If you live in Paris, go to Eiffel tower and draw it instead of drawing pyramids. Just get out of your house and observe nature as it is. Go to some park or coffee shop or any other place where you expect to find people. Initially draw live sketches of inanimate objects and then move on to draw the people as they stand in line to pay or disorganized on a platform while boarding trains.\n\nAfter you have practiced rough sketches, move to permanent. Painting with inks and other permanent media burns down your option to erase when things go wrong but it is an important step if you want to improve your sketching skills. You can learn to drive a car in your neighborhood with less traffic around, but if you are planning to go to work with it- you must practice it in traffic (though only after learning to drive). This is what we are trying to do here, giving you the confidence to draw without having to erase. At first, you will be shy and draw carefully measured lines since you have just lost your ability to erase. But very soon you will lose your internal fear of drawing wrong lines. You will start focusing more on your subject and less on perfecting the lines, just as you focus on street and don\'t search for breaks once you have learned to drive.\n\nAfter your strokes grow bolder you can focus on some refining skills to make your drawings even better. You should try to draw with your non-drawing hand in order to enhance your focus. You should study anatomy to improve your skill level. The knowledge of person\'s build, skeletal structure and joints will help you while drawing people as well as animals. You should look at your subjects as geometrical shapes- square, rectangle, circle etc. this will give you the power to draw fast. Also draw same objects in different poses or angles to enhance your perception of depth.\n\nGiving finishing touch to your skills practice on works by masters. Redrawing works of Picasso, Michelangelo and daVinci will help you more and you will understand the bigger challenges. Happy drawing.","Ways to improve your drawing skills","","publish","open","open","","ways-to-improve-your-drawing-skills","","","2011-04-03 03:37:47","2011-04-03 03:37:47","","0","http://www.nethaat.com/blog/?p=158","0","post","","0");
